{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013TEz8s9jpdSPkhy3dDM1wv","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package engine\n     2→\n     3→import (\n     4→\t\"context\"\n     5→\t\"fmt\"\n     6→\t\"log\"\n     7→\t\"sync\"\n     8→\t\"time\"\n     9→\n    10→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/domain\"\n    11→)\n    12→\n    13→const DefaultStepTimeout = 30 * time.Minute\n    14→\n    15→// StepExecutor executes a single step and returns the result name.\n    16→type StepExecutor interface {\n    17→\tExecute(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step) (string, error)\n    18→}\n    19→\n    20→// StepExecutorFunc adapts a function to the StepExecutor interface.\n    21→type StepExecutorFunc func(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step) (string, error)\n    22→\n    23→func (f StepExecutorFunc) Execute(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step) (string, error) {\n    24→\treturn f(ctx, step)\n    25→}\n    26→\n    27→// StatusHandler receives notifications about workflow execution progress.\n    28→type StatusHandler interface {\n    29→\tOnStepStart(run *domain.Run, step *domain.Step)\n    30→\tOnStepComplete(run *domain.Run, step *domain.Step, result string)\n    31→\tOnRunComplete(run *domain.Run)\n    32→}\n    33→\n    34→type noopStatus struct{}\n    35→\n    36→func (noopStatus) OnStepStart(*domain.Run, *domain.Step)            {}\n    37→func (noopStatus) OnStepComplete(*domain.Run, *domain.Step, string) {}\n    38→func (noopStatus) OnRunComplete(*domain.Run)                        {}\n    39→\n    40→type Engine struct {\n    41→\texecutor       StepExecutor\n    42→\tstatus         StatusHandler\n    43→\tmaxSteps       int\n    44→\tdefaultTimeout time.Duration\n    45→}\n    46→\n    47→func New(executor StepExecutor) *Engine {\n    48→\treturn &Engine{\n    49→\t\texecutor:       executor,\n    50→\t\tstatus:         noopStatus{},\n    51→\t\tmaxSteps:       1000,\n    52→\t\tdefaultTimeout: DefaultStepTimeout,\n    53→\t}\n    54→}\n    55→\n    56→func (e *Engine) SetStatusHandler(h StatusHandler) {\n    57→\te.status = h\n    58→}\n    59→\n    60→func (e *Engine) SetMaxSteps(n int) {\n    61→\te.maxSteps = n\n    62→}\n    63→\n    64→// SetDefaultTimeout sets the default timeout for steps that don't specify one.\n    65→func (e *Engine) SetDefaultTimeout(d time.Duration) {\n    66→\te.defaultTimeout = d\n    67→}\n    68→\n    69→// stepResult is sent from worker goroutines back to the main event loop.\n    70→type stepResult struct {\n    71→\tstepName string\n    72→\tresult   string\n    73→\terr      error\n    74→}\n    75→\n    76→// collectState tracks the satisfaction state of a single Collect clause.\n    77→type collectState struct {\n    78→\tcollect   *domain.Collect\n    79→\tsatisfied map[int]bool\n    80→\tfired     bool\n    81→}\n    82→\n    83→func (e *Engine) Run(ctx context.Context, wf *domain.Workflow) (*domain.Run, error) {\n    84→\tif err := wf.Validate(); err != nil {\n    85→\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"invalid workflow: %w\", err)\n    86→\t}\n    87→\tfor _, w := range wf.ValidateConfig() {\n    88→\t\tlog.Printf(\"WARNING: %s\", w)\n    89→\t}\n    90→\n    91→\trun := domain.NewRun(generateRunID(), wf.Name)\n    92→\trun.Start()\n    93→\n    94→\t// Check context cancellation before starting.\n    95→\tif err := ctx.Err(); err != nil {\n    96→\t\trun.Complete(domain.RunStateCancelled)\n    97→\t\treturn run, fmt.Errorf(\"workflow cancelled: %w\", err)\n    98→\t}\n    99→\n   100→\t// Build a set of (step, result) pairs that are handled by collects,"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_013wwjsqmM3MdrTvaJaJWq2B","session_id":"d5852ca5-8605-4df2-ab4e-a8f4a3409842","uuid":"7fab6627-9a95-41fc-94d2-78d84714b9d3"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013wwjsqmM3MdrTvaJaJWq2B","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me compile a comprehensive summary for the user:\n\n## Summary: Daemon RunWorkflow Handler and Container Image Building\n\nI've thoroughly analyzed the codebase. Here's the complete picture:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **RunWorkflow Request Handler**\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`** (Lines 96-143)\n\nThe `RunWorkflow` RPC handler is the entry point:\n- **Line 96-143**: `RunWorkflow()` method accepts `RunWorkflowRequest` (workflow name, project dir, image, prompt, keep_container flag)\n- **Key flow**:\n  1. Generates unique run ID (lines 102-114)\n  2. Writes prompt to `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt` if provided (lines 117-125)\n  3. Creates Run record in store (lines 126-130)\n  4. Resolves image (request override → server default) (lines 132-136)\n  5. **Launches container in background** via `launchAndTrack()` goroutine (line 140) so RPC returns immediately\n  6. Returns run ID to client\n\n**Background Processing: `launchAndTrack()`** (Lines 148-196)\n- **Line 152-162**: Calls `EnsureImage()` if container runtime implements `ImageEnsurer` interface (auto-rebuild if Dockerfile changed)\n- **Line 164**: Captures git HEAD SHA for result branch creation\n- **Line 166-172**: Calls `container.Start()` with full config\n- **Line 174-181**: Handles start errors, marks run failed\n- **Line 187-193**: Stores container ID and base SHA in run record, marks as Running\n- **Line 195**: Delegates to `trackRun()` for full execution tracking\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Container Image Building Logic**\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/build.go`**\n\n**Main Entry: `EnsureImage()`** (Lines 23-56)\n- Checks if `.cloche/Dockerfile` exists (returns nil if not found—no validation needed)\n- Computes SHA-256 hash of Dockerfile content (line 35)\n- Retrieves stored hash from image labels (line 37)\n- **If image missing or hash mismatch**: calls `buildImage()` (lines 40-45)\n- **If hash matches**: checks if base image is stale (lines 48-52)\n- Logs result (line 54)\n\n**Build Implementation: `buildImage()`** (Lines 160-188)\n- Runs `docker build` with:\n  - `-t <image>` flag to tag the image\n  - `-f <Dockerfile>` to specify the Dockerfile path\n  - Labels embedded for tracking:\n    - `cloche.dockerfile.hash=<SHA-256>` (Dockerfile content hash)\n    - `cloche.baseimage.digest=<image-id>` (base image ID at build time)\n  - Build context: project directory\n- Streams output to daemon stderr (line 180)\n- Returns error on failure\n\n**Image Tracking/Caching Features**:\n\n1. **Dockerfile Hash Label** (`dockerfileHashLabel` = `\"cloche.dockerfile.hash\"`)\n   - Stored on every build (line 167)\n   - Retrieved via `imageLabel()` to detect changes (line 37)\n   - Triggers rebuild when mismatch detected (line 43)\n\n2. **Base Image Digest Label** (`baseImageDigestLabel` = `\"cloche.baseimage.digest\"`)\n   - Captured at build time via `baseImageID()` (lines 171-174)\n   - Tracks the local image ID of the base image (FROM directive)\n   - Detects upstream base image changes (line 49)\n\n**Base Image Change Detection: `isBaseImageStale()`** (Lines 108-130)\n- Parses final FROM directive from Dockerfile (line 109)\n- Retrieves stored base digest from image labels (line 114)\n- Gets current local base image ID (line 120)\n- **Returns true if IDs differ** → triggers rebuild (lines 126-128)\n\n**Helper Functions**:\n- `parseBaseImage()` (Lines 61-84): Extracts final FROM clause, handles multi-stage builds, comments, `--platform` flags\n- `baseImageID()` (Lines 88-101): Gets Docker image ID via `docker inspect`\n- `imageLabel()` (Lines 140-155): Retrieves label from image config\n- `hashBytes()` (Lines 133-136): SHA-256 hash of Dockerfile content\n\n---\n\n### 3. **ContainerRuntime Port/Interface**\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/ports/container.go`**\n\n**`ContainerRuntime` Interface** (Lines 24-33):\n```go\ntype ContainerRuntime interface {\n\tStart(ctx context.Context, cfg ContainerConfig) (containerID string, err error)\n\tStop(ctx context.Context, containerID string) error\n\tAttachOutput(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (io.ReadCloser, error)\n\tWait(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (exitCode int, err error)\n\tCopyFrom(ctx context.Context, containerID string, srcPath, dstPath string) error\n\tLogs(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (string, error)\n\tRemove(ctx context.Context, containerID string) error\n\tInspect(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (*ContainerStatus, error)\n}\n```\n\n**`ImageEnsurer` Optional Interface** (Lines 38-40):\n```go\ntype ImageEnsurer interface {\n\tEnsureImage(ctx context.Context, projectDir, image string) error\n}\n```\n\n**`ContainerConfig` struct** (Lines 15-22):\n- Image, WorkflowName, ProjectDir, NetworkAllow, RunID\n- Optional Cmd override (defaults to `[\"cloche-agent\", \".cloche/<workflow>.cloche\"]`)\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Docker Adapter Implementation**\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go`**\n\n**`Start()` Method** (Lines 27-152):\n1. **Docker create** (lines 35-104):\n   - Default cmd: `[\"cloche-agent\", \".cloche/<workflow>.cloche\"]`\n   - Creates container with:\n     - `--workdir /workspace`\n     - `--add-host host.docker.internal:host-gateway`\n     - `--user root` (for default cmd, then switched to agent user)\n     - Environment: `CLOCHE_RUN_ID`, `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` (if set)\n     - Extra mounts via `CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS` env var\n     - Extra env vars via `CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV` env var\n   - Wraps default cmd with ownership setup and agent user switch\n\n2. **Copy project files** (lines 108-128):\n   - Full project directory copied to `/workspace/` via `docker cp`\n   - `.cloche/overrides/` applied on top (non-fatal if missing)\n\n3. **Copy Claude auth** (lines 131-140):\n   - `~/.claude` directory and `~/.claude.json` copied to container\n\n4. **Start container** (lines 142-151)\n\n**Other Runtime Methods**:\n- `Stop()`: `docker stop` (Lines 154-163)\n- `AttachOutput()`: `docker logs -f` piped to ReadCloser (Lines 165-177)\n- `Wait()`: `docker wait` returns exit code (Lines 179-194)\n- `CopyFrom()`: `docker cp` from container (Lines 196-204)\n- `Logs()`: `docker logs` returns combined stdout+stderr (Lines 206-217)\n- `Remove()`: `docker rm` (Lines 219-227)\n- `Inspect()`: `docker inspect` returns running status, exit code, finished time (Lines 229-255)\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Domain Types**\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`**\n\n**`Run` struct** (Lines 31-44):\n```go\ntype Run struct {\n\tID             string\n\tWorkflowName   string\n\tState          RunState             // pending, running, succeeded, failed, cancelled\n\tActiveSteps    []string\n\tStepExecutions []*StepExecution\n\tStartedAt      time.Time\n\tCompletedAt    time.Time\n\tProjectDir     string\n\tErrorMessage   string\n\tContainerID    string\n\tBaseSHA        string                // Git HEAD at run start\n\tContainerKept  bool\n}\n```\n\n**`StepExecution` struct** (Lines 18-25):\n```go\ntype StepExecution struct {\n\tStepName    string\n\tResult      string\n\tStartedAt   time.Time\n\tCompletedAt time.Time\n\tLogs        string\n\tGitRef      string\n}\n```\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`**\n\n**`Workflow` struct** (Lines 52-59):\n```go\ntype Workflow struct {\n\tName      string\n\tSteps     map[string]*Step\n\tWiring    []Wire\n\tCollects  []Collect\n\tEntryStep string\n\tConfig    map[string]string\n}\n```\n\n**`Step` struct** (Lines 21-26):\n```go\ntype Step struct {\n\tName    string\n\tType    StepType           // agent, script, workflow\n\tResults []string\n\tConfig  map[string]string\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Persistence Layer**\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go`**\n\n**`RunStore` Interface** (Lines 10-18):\n- `CreateRun`, `GetRun`, `UpdateRun`, `DeleteRun`, `ListRuns`, `ListRunsByProject`, `ListProjects`\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go`**\n\n- SQLite database with WAL mode for concurrent access\n- Tables: `runs`, `step_executions`, `log_files`, `merge_queue`, `evolution_log`\n- Run record persisted with all fields (state, container_id, base_sha, error_message, etc.)\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Complete Request Flow**\n\n1. **Client calls `RunWorkflow` RPC** (proto: `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto` lines 18-24)\n2. **gRPC handler** (`server.go:96`) creates run record, returns run ID immediately\n3. **Background goroutine** (`server.go:148`) checks image via `EnsureImage()` (may rebuild)\n4. **Container starts** with full project copied, env vars set\n5. **Container output tracked** (`server.go:198`) — listens to JSON-line status messages\n6. **On completion** (`server.go:198-363`):\n   - Extracts output files\n   - Indexes logs\n   - Extracts results to git branch (worktree)\n   - Handles container retention\n   - Fires evolution trigger if enabled\n   - Calls orchestrator callback\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Build-Related Code Paths**\n\n- **Entry point for image prep**: `server.go:152-162` calls `EnsureImage()`\n- **Build decision logic**: `build.go:23-56` (`EnsureImage()`)\n- **Docker build execution**: `build.go:160-188` (`buildImage()`)\n- **Image staleness checks**:\n  - Dockerfile hash: `build.go:35-46`\n  - Base image digest: `build.go:48-52`\n- **Result extraction**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/extract.go:15-91` (`ExtractResults()`)\n\n---\n\n### **Key Files Summary**\n\n| Purpose | File | Key Lines |\n|---------|------|-----------|\n| RunWorkflow handler | `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` | 96-196 |\n| Image building & caching | `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/build.go` | All |\n| Container runtime (Docker) | `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go` | 27-255 |\n| ContainerRuntime interface | `/workspace/internal/ports/container.go` | 24-40 |