{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_019n36EnerFSWM7Wiq22RK9A","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The feature is already fully implemented. Here's a summary of what's in place:\n\n## Existing Implementation (already complete)\n\n### Staleness Detection (`internal/adapters/docker/build.go`)\n- **`EnsureImage()`** — checks if the container image is up-to-date before a run:\n  1. Computes SHA-256 of `.cloche/Dockerfile` content\n  2. Compares against hash stored in the image's `cloche.dockerfile.hash` label\n  3. If Dockerfile hash matches, also checks base image staleness via `isBaseImageStale()` — compares stored `cloche.baseimage.digest` label against current local base image ID\n  4. Rebuilds automatically if any mismatch is found\n\n### Integration in Daemon (`internal/adapters/grpc/server.go:152-162`)\n- `launchAndTrack()` calls `EnsureImage()` (via `ImageEnsurer` interface) **before** `container.Start()` when processing a `RunWorkflow` request\n- On rebuild failure, the run is marked as failed with a descriptive error\n\n### Port Interface (`internal/ports/container.go:38-40`)\n- `ImageEnsurer` is an optional interface that `ContainerRuntime` can implement\n\n### Tests\n- **`build_test.go`**: 8 tests covering hash computation, no-Dockerfile case, build-on-missing, skip-when-up-to-date, Dockerfile change detection, base image digest storage, `parseBaseImage` (8 subtests), and stale-label handling\n- **`server_test.go`**: `TestServer_RunWorkflow_CallsEnsureImage` verifies `EnsureImage` is called during `RunWorkflow`; `TestServer_RunWorkflow_EnsureImageFailure` verifies the run is marked failed when image build fails\n\nNo code changes are needed — the task requirements are already satisfied by the existing implementation."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1178,"cache_read_input_tokens":32733,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens"